         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8 April 1870 ¶  ¶ [Director recommends that the Inspr of Forests ¶ William Ferguson. ¶  ¶ may be placed under the Lands Dept with a view of commencing an inspection of the principal forests of this Co...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.04.08<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John MacPherson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 3559, vol. 1870 W, VPRS 1168/P inward correspondence registers, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Trans 24.1.94. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found; item is a register entry only,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">dated</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>8 April 1870.</p>
               </note>8 April 1870</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Director recommends that the Inspr of Forests<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>William Ferguson.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>may be placed under the Lands Dept with a view of commencing an inspection of the principal forests of this Colony<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See notes to W. Odgers to M, 24 March 1870,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the text of an enclosed letter to William Ferguson. The letter<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from Odgers<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to Ferguson included 'it would be well for you to hold yourself in readiness to actively engage in the work of Inspection of Forests as soon as suitable weather sets in'. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It is probable that M knew the content of the letter and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>may have acted when the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>weather at the end of March and the first week of April was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>generally<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'dry and warm'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and 'warm and sultry' (Government Astronomers reports,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 4 April 1870, p. 5,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>11 April<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1870, p. 5).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M's letter<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was referred to the Commissioner of Crown Lands on 12 April 1870 and returned to the Chief Secretary's Department on 21 April.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">Was it approved?</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">Ferguson was still subordinate to M when<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>C. Hodgkinson to M, 21 April 1870 asked M to instruct Ferguson to visit Bullarook Forest.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>His report is at Ballarat Star 20 October 1870, p. 2<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">But he was still<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">at Gardens as curator in 1872, transferring to Macedon by 1 November, see note 8 to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="HTMLCite" style="font-style: normal; color: #C00000; ">72-09-16</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">Fergusson's report as Inspector of forests <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Vic Parl Paper <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1871 C 9</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>
                        </seg>
                        <ref target="https://pov.ent.sirsidynix.net.au/client/en_GB/parl_paper/search/detailnonmodal/ent:$002f$002fSD_ILS$002f0$002fSD_ILS:66781/one">
                           <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #467886; ">https://pov.ent.sirsidynix.net.au/client/en_GB/parl_paper/search/detailnonmodal/ent:$002f$002fSD_ILS$002f0$002fSD_ILS:66781/one</seg>
                        </ref>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and go to bottom and open pdf shows he was ardered by Hodgkinson top male other inspections during 1870</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>]</p>
         </div>
      </body>
